\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506   2. The system evaluates the  business logic and priority rules.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506   3. The system overrides the existing data to prioritize the high-priority user.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506   4. A trigger system activates to send a conflict notification to the lower-priority user, informing them of the cancellation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\cf20\insrsid5197426\charrsid862242 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506   - System Architecture Support:
